WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:02.334
You're a liar.

00:02.336 --> 00:05.537
Yeah, this is Nero.
The handsome one from the party.

00:05.539 --> 00:08.206
Neighborhood boy got
hisself murdered.

00:08.208 --> 00:10.743
-What's your name?
-I'm Jay Singletary.

00:10.745 --> 00:12.144
Are you
Tamar's daughter?

00:13.948 --> 00:16.414
Jay:
I just got rousted really bad
by the LAPD.

00:16.416 --> 00:17.682
[ Grunting ]

00:17.684 --> 00:19.484
Why in the hell
would they do that

00:19.486 --> 00:22.955
if there wasn't
a story to follow?

00:22.957 --> 00:24.957
Fauna: There's something
going on, Terrence.

00:24.959 --> 00:27.091
I can't stay here.

00:27.093 --> 00:30.028
If you go looking for trouble,
you'll find it.

00:30.030 --> 00:32.531
The Hodel thing,
it's real.

00:34.769 --> 00:37.202
♪♪

00:38.973 --> 00:41.540
♪♪

00:44.911 --> 00:48.513
Producer Chet:
Nice night, huh?

00:48.515 --> 00:52.184
Starlet: Are you friends
with Dr. Hodel?

00:52.186 --> 00:53.786
He's a genius, right?

00:53.788 --> 00:55.454
Best doctor
in the city.

00:55.456 --> 00:57.256
Maybe the country, right?

00:59.726 --> 01:02.294
♪♪

01:10.270 --> 01:14.373
♪♪

01:16.543 --> 01:18.943
Mate in four.

01:18.945 --> 01:21.613
I'm very disappointed
you lost her.

01:21.615 --> 01:22.815
The city isn't safe,

01:22.817 --> 01:25.818
not for
someone like that.

01:25.820 --> 01:29.154
Well, now
it's mate in two.

01:29.156 --> 01:32.090
There's no way out,
friend.

01:32.092 --> 01:35.494
Dr. Hodel?

01:35.496 --> 01:39.297
Ah, yes. 8:00.

01:39.299 --> 01:41.233
Sepp -- find her.

01:44.371 --> 01:45.303
[ Glass thuds ]

01:45.305 --> 01:46.839
Find her.

01:51.045 --> 01:52.310
Sit.

01:52.312 --> 01:54.680
♪♪

01:59.786 --> 02:02.521
Well, I-I guess you'll have
plenty of time

02:02.523 --> 02:05.524
to figure out your next move.

02:05.526 --> 02:08.527
No.

02:08.529 --> 02:10.595
I'm gonna
spoil his game.

02:10.597 --> 02:12.231
♪♪

02:19.673 --> 02:21.640
♪♪

02:28.949 --> 02:31.350
♪♪

02:38.225 --> 02:40.059
♪♪

02:47.234 --> 02:49.702
♪♪

02:56.310 --> 02:58.177
♪♪

03:07.521 --> 03:10.322
[ Siren wails in distance ]

03:16.396 --> 03:18.697
♪♪

03:24.471 --> 03:26.538
♪♪

03:30.277 --> 03:32.411
♪♪

03:33.680 --> 03:36.615
[ Telephone ringing ]

03:44.424 --> 03:46.158
Yeah?

03:46.160 --> 03:49.762
Corinna:<i>Hello?</i>

03:49.764 --> 03:51.597
<i> I know who you are.</i>

03:53.567 --> 03:55.367
<i> Do you know who I am?</i>

03:57.838 --> 03:59.437
This is...

03:59.439 --> 04:02.307
Corinna Hodel.

04:02.309 --> 04:04.343
[ Chuckling ]

04:10.050 --> 04:13.619
<i> You -- You wanna know</i>
<i> something?</i>

04:16.323 --> 04:18.123
[ Voice breaking ]
I'll show you something.

04:21.328 --> 04:22.927
I'll tell you something.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.262
[ Sobbing ]

04:24.264 --> 04:26.265
[<i>Chuckling</i>]

04:27.534 --> 04:28.667
[ Telephone clicks ]

04:28.669 --> 04:30.202
[ Dial tone ]

04:33.340 --> 04:36.875
Children:
♪ Teddy bear, teddy bear,
turn around! ♪

04:36.877 --> 04:39.211
♪ Teddy bear, teddy bear,
touch the -- ♪

04:39.213 --> 04:41.013
You didn't
touch the ground!

04:41.015 --> 04:43.816
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:43.818 --> 04:46.084
Hey, what's going on,
Frank?

04:46.086 --> 04:48.286
-Oh, my goodness.
-Yeah, how you doing?

04:48.288 --> 04:51.991
-How you guys doing?
-Hey, man, I'm -- I'm glad...

04:53.093 --> 04:54.559
Man: Hey, I got it --
I got it right here.

04:54.561 --> 04:55.960
This is good.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.630
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

04:58.632 --> 05:02.100
Hey, man,
maybe you can help me out.

05:02.102 --> 05:04.169
♪♪

05:06.907 --> 05:09.641
-Ah, really?
-Yeah, that's all of it.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.176
-Yeah.
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.

05:11.178 --> 05:13.645
Fauna: N-No, ma'am.
I'm in Los Angeles.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.781
Could you tell Lewis...?

05:18.585 --> 05:22.987
Can you please tell Lewis
that I-I miss him?

05:22.989 --> 05:25.790
Thank you.

05:25.792 --> 05:27.526
Goodbye, ma'am.

05:27.528 --> 05:29.595
♪♪

05:33.734 --> 05:35.968
[ Door opens ]

05:39.273 --> 05:40.372
Good morning.

05:42.676 --> 05:44.276
You all right?

05:44.278 --> 05:45.810
Good morning.

05:45.812 --> 05:46.945
Yes, fine, thanks.

05:46.947 --> 05:49.748
Thank you.

05:49.750 --> 05:51.816
You sure work hard
on that car.

05:51.818 --> 05:53.552
Didn't know
you liked cars so much.

05:53.554 --> 05:55.420
No, I hate cars.

05:55.422 --> 05:58.290
I hate that car
in particular, but...

05:58.292 --> 06:00.158
without that car,
it's nearly three hours

06:00.160 --> 06:01.426
on the bus
to work and school.

06:01.428 --> 06:03.095
Can't be done.

06:03.097 --> 06:05.163
[ Scoffs ]
I had a flat tire.

06:05.165 --> 06:06.298
12 minutes late,

06:06.300 --> 06:08.166
and the manager
lodged a complaint.

06:08.168 --> 06:10.769
Boy, was he happy
to have a reason.

06:10.771 --> 06:12.571
All I want to think about
is propulsion.

06:12.573 --> 06:15.908
Some white men take it personal,
like me tryin' to succeed

06:15.910 --> 06:18.110
is taking something
from them.

06:18.112 --> 06:20.779
[ Faucet squeaks, water runs ]

06:20.781 --> 06:22.915
Aren't they all
like that?

06:22.917 --> 06:24.516
[ Water shuts off ]
No.

06:24.518 --> 06:26.085
Some don't mind.

06:27.788 --> 06:30.388
It's Sunday.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.257
I got some errands.
What do you need to do today?

06:32.259 --> 06:35.727
I'm...
gonna keep looking, I guess.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.062
Can't let it go?

06:38.064 --> 06:40.332
What if he's wonderful?

06:40.334 --> 06:44.136
Or what if
he needs my help?

06:44.138 --> 06:47.739
Would you stop
before you knew?

06:47.741 --> 06:51.009
I guess not.

06:51.011 --> 06:52.544
I'll take you to the bus.

06:54.481 --> 06:57.016
But, uh, there's one thing
we got to do first.

07:01.088 --> 07:03.756
Jay: So, you're back
on the beat, huh?

07:03.758 --> 07:06.091
Ohls:
It is what it is.

07:06.093 --> 07:08.360
An hour and a half
commute.

07:08.362 --> 07:10.295
I think about my life.

07:10.297 --> 07:12.430
I listen to the Beatles,
try to figure out

07:12.432 --> 07:14.098
what makes the girls
scream like that.

07:14.100 --> 07:15.367
-[ Chuckles ]
-Right?

07:15.369 --> 07:18.837
Look, Ohls, I'm, uh...
I'm sorry.

07:18.839 --> 07:22.307
No, no, no, Jay,
it is what it is.

07:22.309 --> 07:24.509
We're never
gonna be square.

07:24.511 --> 07:26.645
I'm gonna take a shit.
-That's nice.

07:26.647 --> 07:30.182
Yeah, it's the nicest toilet
we'll see today.

07:30.184 --> 07:32.484
Talk to Miller.
He's a four-fifteen.

07:33.988 --> 07:35.253
Mmm.

07:35.255 --> 07:38.590
So, what's, uh --
What's a four-fifteen?

07:38.592 --> 07:41.393
Penal code,
disturbing the peace.

07:41.395 --> 07:42.661
[ Both chuckle ]

07:42.663 --> 07:44.330
He's kiddin'.

07:46.266 --> 07:49.267
Why the hell
aren't you retired?

07:49.269 --> 07:51.336
I've been in 32 years.

07:51.338 --> 07:53.938
Oldest living cop
in captivity.

07:53.940 --> 07:56.208
I could retire,

07:56.210 --> 07:59.044
but I'd start drinking
and never stop.

08:00.815 --> 08:02.547
I done it all, son.

08:02.549 --> 08:07.752
Robbery-homicide,
juvenile, vice, aah...

08:07.754 --> 08:11.623
So, do you remember
the Black Dahlia murder?

08:11.625 --> 08:13.025
Of course! Sure!

08:13.027 --> 08:14.226
Wouldn't be an LA cop

08:14.228 --> 08:16.495
if I didn't have
my own Dahlia story.

08:16.497 --> 08:18.497
Yeah.

08:18.499 --> 08:20.365
I knocked on doors.

08:20.367 --> 08:22.835
We called it
the "werewolf"

08:22.837 --> 08:27.039
until the Black Dahlia
name hit.

08:27.041 --> 08:29.774
You ever hear
of a copycat?

08:29.776 --> 08:31.243
Copycat?
Yeah.

08:31.245 --> 08:33.245
Nah!

08:33.247 --> 08:34.779
Nothing sticks out.

08:34.781 --> 08:35.914
No?
No.

08:35.916 --> 08:38.783
<i> She</i>was unique.

08:38.785 --> 08:43.188
Ohh, whew, aah, [Chuckles]
you seen the pictures, right?

08:43.190 --> 08:44.656
Uh-huh.

08:44.658 --> 08:47.592
I-I remember thinking,

08:47.594 --> 08:50.795
"He musta hated her
to do what he did to her."

08:50.797 --> 08:52.865
You think so?

08:52.867 --> 08:54.933
Chop her in half?

08:54.935 --> 08:56.334
Her face?

08:56.336 --> 09:01.806
Ohh, well, he hated her
pretty good, you ask me.

09:01.808 --> 09:03.375
Yeah, I don't, uh...

09:04.611 --> 09:05.878
♪♪

09:08.348 --> 09:09.481
It doesn't
look like hate.

09:09.483 --> 09:11.083
It looks like
something else.

09:11.085 --> 09:13.585
♪♪

09:16.623 --> 09:18.657
♪♪

09:21.762 --> 09:23.027
[ Sighs ]

09:23.029 --> 09:24.396
♪♪

09:32.573 --> 09:34.573
♪♪

09:42.048 --> 09:44.149
♪♪

09:51.592 --> 09:54.159
♪♪

10:23.090 --> 10:24.890
[ Engine shuts off ]

10:24.892 --> 10:26.992
♪♪

10:31.364 --> 10:33.766
♪♪

10:37.705 --> 10:38.837
[ Sighs ]

10:38.839 --> 10:40.606
What are we doing here?

10:42.976 --> 10:44.943
Starts in laughter,
ends in tears.

10:49.316 --> 10:51.516
What is that?

10:51.518 --> 10:53.919
We're tipping Nero.

10:53.921 --> 10:56.588
This is where
they found him.

10:56.590 --> 10:58.257
[ Sighs deeply ]

10:58.259 --> 10:59.991
It's actually an ancient
Egyptian practice

10:59.993 --> 11:02.127
called "libation".

11:02.129 --> 11:04.096
Pre-dates Christianity.

11:07.468 --> 11:09.134
Were you friends
with Nero?

11:09.136 --> 11:11.069
We ran a little as kids,

11:11.071 --> 11:12.938
had a little clique
tied up with Slausons,

11:12.940 --> 11:15.074
but Nero didn't have
no real friends.

11:18.746 --> 11:21.012
But look at this.
It's -- There's no crime scene.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.948
It's nothing.

11:25.953 --> 11:28.887
I'm sorry.

11:28.889 --> 11:29.955
Yeah.

11:29.957 --> 11:32.891
Not as sorry as Nero.

11:32.893 --> 11:34.293
There's no one
to cry for Nero.

11:34.295 --> 11:36.762
So, how was he supposed to be
any different?

11:36.764 --> 11:39.230
No pops,
mom's on the street.

11:39.232 --> 11:41.766
She used to keep him
locked in for days at a time.

11:41.768 --> 11:43.768
I came in on him once,
and he had a busted foot,

11:43.770 --> 11:45.436
all swole.

11:45.438 --> 11:49.174
Been left alone in there
for two days.

11:49.176 --> 11:52.377
He was eight years old.

11:52.379 --> 11:55.180
How was he supposed to end up
any different than he was?

11:58.251 --> 11:59.985
[ Glass shatters ]

11:59.987 --> 12:01.853
Hey!

12:01.855 --> 12:03.722
What's wrong with you?!

12:03.724 --> 12:05.524
Why you throwing shit
around my house?

12:05.526 --> 12:07.726
I'm sorry, man.
I -- All right, we're sorry.

12:07.728 --> 12:11.930
You see me throwing shit
around your house?

12:11.932 --> 12:13.198
Hey, man.

12:13.200 --> 12:14.933
Hey, buddy.
You live here?

12:14.935 --> 12:17.336
You see the fuzz come in here?

12:17.338 --> 12:19.938
Yeah, Brunos
with their buzzers.

12:19.940 --> 12:21.272
[ Spits ]

12:21.274 --> 12:23.274
You see anything else?

12:23.276 --> 12:24.743
I seen lots.

12:24.745 --> 12:29.614
I seen a man park his
big, black, shiny Buick up there

12:29.616 --> 12:33.152
and get out, walk around
like he own the place.

12:33.154 --> 12:36.888
I told
the police, too.

12:36.890 --> 12:42.227
I seen One-Eye Mexican Carlos --
He kick a dog to death.

12:42.229 --> 12:44.696
Man,
that ain't right.

12:44.698 --> 12:46.765
He's a mean
son of a bitch.

12:52.239 --> 12:54.039
♪♪

12:54.041 --> 12:54.105
♪♪
Hey.

12:54.307 --> 12:55.240
Hey.

12:55.242 --> 12:57.442
Didn't you say something

12:57.444 --> 12:59.378
about a white man
in a Buick?

13:02.315 --> 13:04.783
I don't know what's going on,
Terrence.

13:04.785 --> 13:07.719
I don't.

13:07.721 --> 13:11.723
There's a man -- a man
who follows me around sometimes.

13:11.725 --> 13:14.659
I swear to God
I don't know why.

13:14.661 --> 13:19.130
And, yeah, he drives a Buick,
but I barely knew Nero.

13:19.132 --> 13:20.932
Yeah. Yeah, right.
It's just Nero.

13:20.934 --> 13:22.333
Who cares?

13:22.335 --> 13:24.003
Terrence, please.
I got nothing to do with this.

13:24.005 --> 13:27.406
You got nothing
to do with it?

13:27.408 --> 13:29.508
You got something
to do with it.

13:31.278 --> 13:32.644
[ Keys jingle,
engine turns over ]

13:34.681 --> 13:37.349
♪♪

13:48.361 --> 13:51.096
♪♪

13:58.505 --> 14:00.539
♪♪

14:08.181 --> 14:09.748
♪♪

14:15.589 --> 14:17.823
♪♪

14:23.597 --> 14:27.132
Well, look
what the cat drug in.

14:27.134 --> 14:28.934
Hi, Big Momma.
I-I'm sorry I --

14:28.936 --> 14:32.003
What kinda place do you think
I'm running here?

14:32.005 --> 14:35.540
Jimmy Lee called
so angry,

14:35.542 --> 14:40.512
and now she's coming to
Los Angeles<i>tonight.</i>

14:50.891 --> 14:54.293
Where you at Terrence's place
last night?

14:54.295 --> 14:56.762
Nothing happened.
It wasn't like that.

14:56.764 --> 14:59.230
Well, damn, girl,
you move fast.

14:59.232 --> 15:00.632
You only been here
a few days

15:00.634 --> 15:02.768
and already moving in
on a boy like that?

15:02.770 --> 15:05.304
You a fast mover.

15:05.306 --> 15:09.374
Tina, I was just scared
because of Nero.

15:09.376 --> 15:10.709
And --
And what?

15:10.711 --> 15:12.377
You thought Terrence's
big, strong arms

15:12.379 --> 15:14.480
was gonna
keep you safe?

15:17.118 --> 15:20.051
Well, Terrence ain't
much my type anyway.

15:20.053 --> 15:21.787
He have a little stick
up his ass for me,

15:21.789 --> 15:23.555
but I can see it.

15:25.659 --> 15:27.593
This came for you
today.

15:29.530 --> 15:32.263
Xander said
a white man brung it,

15:32.265 --> 15:33.499
but I didn't see him.

15:36.737 --> 15:38.203
Thanks, Tina.

15:38.205 --> 15:40.172
You're welcome.

15:52.019 --> 15:53.152
A happening?

15:53.154 --> 15:55.254
♪♪

16:00.093 --> 16:02.361
[ Brakes squeal ]

16:02.363 --> 16:04.295
[ Engine shuts off ]
Jesus, Jay.

16:04.297 --> 16:06.498
Jay: Peter. Peter.

16:06.500 --> 16:07.966
Just tell -- tell Eddy
it's never gonna happen.

16:07.968 --> 16:09.234
Peter: You know what,
give Eddy a month,

16:09.236 --> 16:10.569
he'll forget all about it.

16:10.571 --> 16:12.237
Just, uh -- uh, wait,
Peter, listen.

16:12.239 --> 16:14.039
The -- The Bloody Romeo thing --
I'm going ass backwards on it

16:14.041 --> 16:16.107
'cause the deeper I dig,
the dumber I get.
Yeah, you know what,

16:16.109 --> 16:18.443
I needed that
like 16 hours ago.
There's this copycat angle.

16:18.445 --> 16:20.645
There's this copycat angle.
You know what, go for it, Jay,
but I can't assign it.

16:20.647 --> 16:22.113
What about the Hodel thing?
There's something there.

16:22.115 --> 16:23.849
I can taste it.
The ex-wife -- she's calling me.

16:23.851 --> 16:25.851
I can feel it.
She's gonna talk.
Damn it, Jay, no,

16:25.853 --> 16:27.318
God damn it.
-I can feel it, Peter.

16:27.320 --> 16:28.520
Don't talk to me
about this stuff.

16:28.522 --> 16:30.255
God damn it, enough.

16:30.257 --> 16:32.191
♪♪

16:37.598 --> 16:39.664
Hey.
-Huh?

16:39.666 --> 16:41.000
You really think
she wants to talk?

16:41.002 --> 16:42.601
Ohh, Peter.

16:42.603 --> 16:46.738
She's calling me in
the middle of the
night, she's crying.

16:46.740 --> 16:48.207
Look.

16:48.209 --> 16:49.975
That came across
the Art Desk.

16:52.546 --> 16:54.546
What's a "Happening"?

16:54.548 --> 16:57.749
[ The Rolling Stones'
"Play With Fire" plays ]

16:57.751 --> 17:00.019
♪♪

17:03.024 --> 17:06.558
♪ Well, you've got
your diamonds ♪

17:06.560 --> 17:10.762
♪ And you've got
your pretty clothes ♪

17:10.764 --> 17:14.900
♪ And the chauffeur
drives your car ♪

17:14.902 --> 17:19.170
♪ You let everybody know ♪

17:19.172 --> 17:22.774
♪ But don't play with me ♪

17:22.776 --> 17:28.714
♪ 'Cause you're playing
with fire ♪

17:28.716 --> 17:32.183
♪ Your mother,
she's an heiress ♪

17:32.185 --> 17:36.588
♪ Owns a block
in Saint John's Wood ♪

17:36.590 --> 17:42.327
♪ And your father'd
be there with her ♪

17:42.329 --> 17:45.597
♪ If he only could ♪

17:45.599 --> 17:49.000
♪ But don't play with me ♪

17:49.002 --> 17:52.203
♪ 'Cause you're playing
with fire ♪

17:52.205 --> 17:55.206
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:55.208 --> 17:58.344
♪♪

18:04.084 --> 18:07.352
♪ Your old man
took her diamonds ♪

18:07.354 --> 18:11.823
♪ And tiaras by the score ♪

18:11.825 --> 18:15.894
♪ Now she gets her kicks
in Stepney ♪

18:15.896 --> 18:17.763
School night,
isn't it?

18:17.765 --> 18:19.364
[ Laughing ]

18:19.366 --> 18:21.232
You lost, sweetheart?

18:21.234 --> 18:24.303
I'm looking for my grandmother.
Corinna Huntington?

18:24.305 --> 18:28.239
Grandmother?
What's your name, hon?

18:28.241 --> 18:30.776
Fauna Hodel.

18:30.778 --> 18:32.444
Oh, yeah?

18:32.446 --> 18:34.313
Whaddaya know?

18:36.117 --> 18:38.783
Hey, Jane!
How's kicks?

18:38.785 --> 18:41.186
Screw off, Bob. Talk to me
when I've had six drinks.

18:41.188 --> 18:42.387
[ Bob laughs ]

18:42.389 --> 18:44.055
I met
your grandfather, too.

18:44.057 --> 18:46.725
I think Corinna's gonna be
in Room Three.

18:46.727 --> 18:49.460
I hate that
pretentious shit, myself.

18:49.462 --> 18:51.596
Did you know Tamar?

18:51.598 --> 18:54.065
I've heard of her.

18:54.067 --> 18:57.669
Did you know Tamar?
What -- What
have you heard?

18:57.671 --> 19:00.339
Six drinks?
C'mon, I'm so bored.
Blow, Bob. I'm in the middle
of something here.

19:00.341 --> 19:03.142
My socks fell off.
Six drinks -- It's gonna take
15 minutes for six drinks.

19:03.144 --> 19:05.544
Bob, blow. Beat it.
-Come on. I'm bored!

19:05.546 --> 19:06.812
How many times do I have to
say, "Beat it"?

19:06.814 --> 19:09.480
Go find someone else
to drink with, Bob.

19:09.482 --> 19:10.749
