23:10.758 --> 23:13.358
Oh. Fauna.

23:13.360 --> 23:15.494
Come in.
Have a seat.

23:15.496 --> 23:17.596
♪♪

23:20.567 --> 23:23.835
Ma'am, I-I wanted to
apologize

23:23.837 --> 23:25.304
for what I said
in the car.

23:25.306 --> 23:26.638
Yes, yes.

23:26.640 --> 23:29.440
I can't remember.

23:29.442 --> 23:31.076
I-It's all so...

23:33.847 --> 23:36.648
Ma'am, I need more.

23:36.650 --> 23:39.718
Can you please tell me
my father's name?

23:39.720 --> 23:43.322
The ballet dancer?

23:43.324 --> 23:45.924
Did you like the piece?

23:45.926 --> 23:49.461
My "Happening"?

23:49.463 --> 23:50.796
N-No, ma'am.

23:50.798 --> 23:52.598
[ Chuckling ]

23:56.870 --> 23:59.270
Avant-garde
needs courage.

23:59.272 --> 24:02.474
Do you know what
that word means --

24:02.476 --> 24:03.776
avant-garde?

24:05.813 --> 24:07.813
No, ma'am.

24:07.815 --> 24:10.149
Think of it as

24:10.151 --> 24:15.286
a term for an advanced,
profound conscience,

24:15.288 --> 24:19.892
based on a deeper
understanding of history.

24:24.031 --> 24:26.699
It takes hard work
and study.

24:28.435 --> 24:33.872
We have another word for art
that is easy to enjoy --

24:37.711 --> 24:41.046
kitsch.

24:41.048 --> 24:44.516
Like a television show.

24:44.518 --> 24:46.986
So, was it just me

24:46.988 --> 24:50.422
getting my clothes
snipped off?

24:52.526 --> 24:53.525
Yes, ma'am.

24:53.527 --> 24:56.461
There is nothing worse
in this world

24:56.463 --> 24:58.329
than
a literalist thinker.

24:58.331 --> 24:59.330
Willful stupidity.

24:59.332 --> 25:01.933
I hate talking after
these things.

25:01.935 --> 25:06.205
Do you even know
what that word means?

25:06.207 --> 25:08.807
"Literalist".

25:08.809 --> 25:10.942
Yes, ma'am.

25:10.944 --> 25:12.211
It's like when
the President said that,

25:12.213 --> 25:15.547
"America has tossed its cap
over the wall into space."

25:15.549 --> 25:20.619
He wasn't talking about
a real wall or a real cap.

25:20.621 --> 25:23.088
And for your show,

25:23.090 --> 25:26.558
I think you just wanted for us
to be responsible for you.

25:26.560 --> 25:30.361
Joining in, or even just
watching, doing nothing.

25:30.363 --> 25:33.132
Either way, you would have been
the one getting hurt.

25:35.836 --> 25:38.770
Smarter than your mother
ever was.

25:38.772 --> 25:41.973
Mrs. Hodel --
Um, Mrs. Huntington,

25:41.975 --> 25:44.976
I need to talk to you
about Tamar.

25:44.978 --> 25:47.178
I'm sorry.
I can't stay here, child.

25:47.180 --> 25:48.847
Surely you understand
that.

25:48.849 --> 25:51.116
♪♪

25:57.658 --> 26:00.426
♪♪

26:06.399 --> 26:09.468
Fauna: Not Tamar.
Not Hodel.

26:12.473 --> 26:14.206
Apate.

26:16.343 --> 26:17.876
But why?

26:17.878 --> 26:20.279
♪♪

26:25.686 --> 26:27.820
Aah!
[ Thud ]

26:33.160 --> 26:34.293
[ Moans ]

26:36.463 --> 26:38.330
[ Gasps, screams ]
Sepp: All right,
now, quiet, quiet!

26:38.332 --> 26:40.398
Hey, Quiet now. Quiet.

26:40.400 --> 26:43.268
Oh, I'd like to slice off
your calf and fry it up

26:43.270 --> 26:45.537
and eat it and puke it up
in front of you.

26:45.539 --> 26:46.739
[ Muffled whimpering ]

26:46.741 --> 26:48.407
You think
he has everything?

26:48.409 --> 26:50.275
He knows everything?

26:50.277 --> 26:52.811
I have something
he doesn't know.

26:52.813 --> 26:55.747
I've been places
he's afraid of.

26:55.749 --> 26:57.682
I'll show him a curse.

26:57.684 --> 26:59.484
I'm ready for the next step.

26:59.486 --> 27:01.219
[ Whimpering continues ]

27:01.221 --> 27:02.687
That's what this is --

27:02.689 --> 27:06.058
my own little show,
the real happening.

27:07.561 --> 27:09.128
[ Knife clatters ]

27:10.497 --> 27:12.030
Shit!

27:12.032 --> 27:14.499
[ Both men groan ]

27:14.501 --> 27:16.301
[ Both men grunting ]

27:16.303 --> 27:18.270
♪♪

27:23.243 --> 27:25.978
♪♪

27:30.384 --> 27:32.116
Start screaming.

27:32.118 --> 27:33.385
You should.
I'll gut --

27:33.387 --> 27:35.520
gut you before
they get down the stairs.

27:35.522 --> 27:38.257
♪♪

27:40.594 --> 27:42.594
Whoo! Whoo!

27:43.998 --> 27:45.097
Ohh!

27:47.001 --> 27:49.267
-Ahhh!
-[ Grunts ]

27:49.269 --> 27:53.072
-[ Choking ]
-[ Breathing heavily ]

27:56.877 --> 27:58.811
[ Grunts ]
[ Knife thuds ]

27:58.813 --> 28:00.945
[ Choking ]

28:00.947 --> 28:04.282
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:04.284 --> 28:06.352
♪♪

28:10.825 --> 28:13.258
♪♪

28:17.297 --> 28:19.498
[ Continues
breathing heavily ]

28:19.500 --> 28:22.601
♪♪

28:28.108 --> 28:30.509
♪♪

28:36.783 --> 28:39.184
[<i>Growling, thumping</i>]

28:43.057 --> 28:45.724
[<i>Growling, thumping continues</i>]

28:45.726 --> 28:48.093
♪♪

28:54.068 --> 28:56.502
♪♪

29:02.342 --> 29:05.344
♪♪

29:10.684 --> 29:11.884
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:11.886 --> 29:13.852
Reporter.

29:16.691 --> 29:18.691
[ Slurred ]
Are you all right?

29:22.028 --> 29:23.361
I'm fine.

29:23.363 --> 29:24.963
[ Door opens ]

29:24.965 --> 29:28.433
[ Faint laughter ]

29:28.435 --> 29:30.302
[ Door closes ]

29:30.304 --> 29:31.570
[ Groans ]

29:31.572 --> 29:34.707
Should we...?

29:34.709 --> 29:36.909
Yeah.

29:36.911 --> 29:41.780
What do we...

29:41.782 --> 29:43.848
-Whoop! Sorry!
-Ohh!

29:43.850 --> 29:45.717
Oh, didn't realize anybody
was down here.

29:45.719 --> 29:47.119
Hi, Fauna.

29:47.121 --> 29:49.654
Oh, what's --
Is that guy okay?

29:49.656 --> 29:51.189
What's wrong with that guy?
-Yeah, he's fine.

29:51.191 --> 29:53.191
He just had a little bit
too much to drink is all.

29:53.193 --> 29:55.193
-A lot of things to drink.
-Let's go find another room.

29:55.195 --> 29:57.262
-He got tired.
-Come on, sweet pea.

29:57.264 --> 29:59.998
-[ Giggles ] All right.
-Come on.

30:00.000 --> 30:02.067
[ Indistinct talking ]

30:05.005 --> 30:07.439
[ Door opens, shuts ]

30:13.480 --> 30:14.813
[ Sniffles ]

30:14.815 --> 30:17.116
They -- They saw me.

30:19.820 --> 30:22.354
Come on. Let's go.

30:22.356 --> 30:24.123
They saw me.

30:26.026 --> 30:27.960
They saw me, too.

30:27.962 --> 30:30.028
She said my name!

30:30.030 --> 30:33.532
We got to --
We got to clean this place up.

30:37.772 --> 30:39.304
Come on. Help me.

30:39.306 --> 30:41.239
We'll roll him up
in this.

30:41.241 --> 30:43.308
♪♪

30:46.246 --> 30:48.913
Let's just go.
Please.

30:48.915 --> 30:50.783
We can't!

30:50.785 --> 30:53.852
They saw me
and she said my name,

30:53.854 --> 30:54.787
and she saw you, too.

30:54.789 --> 30:57.589
You --
Can you help me?

30:57.591 --> 30:59.792
♪♪

31:03.597 --> 31:05.931
♪♪

31:09.470 --> 31:11.170
[ Sighs ]

31:13.607 --> 31:15.607
All right, let me think.

31:15.609 --> 31:18.911
♪♪

31:24.351 --> 31:26.785
♪♪

31:32.827 --> 31:34.159
[ Grunts ]

31:34.161 --> 31:36.261
♪♪

31:41.768 --> 31:43.569
♪♪

31:49.576 --> 31:51.210
Maybe we should drive.

31:54.849 --> 31:56.482
Ahh.

31:59.453 --> 32:02.320
I don't think that's how
you make a gin and tonic.

32:02.322 --> 32:04.656
Do I look like
a bartender?

32:04.658 --> 32:06.391
[ Tires squeal ]

32:06.393 --> 32:08.460
I know where
we can take him.

32:08.462 --> 32:10.062
Great.

32:10.064 --> 32:11.797
♪♪

32:17.804 --> 32:19.505
♪♪

32:25.212 --> 32:26.679
[ Engine shuts off ]

32:26.681 --> 32:28.514
♪♪

32:35.622 --> 32:37.656
[ Slurring ]
All right, let's get
this over with.

32:38.893 --> 32:40.358
[ Grunting ]

32:40.360 --> 32:42.328
[ Breathing heavily ]

32:45.966 --> 32:47.699
You...

32:47.701 --> 32:50.469
♪♪

32:55.175 --> 32:56.841
[ Sighs ] Come on.
Let's go.

32:56.843 --> 32:58.510
No, wait, wait, wait.

32:58.512 --> 32:59.578
Huh?

32:59.580 --> 33:01.113
We got to find out
who he is.

33:01.115 --> 33:02.915
He knows
my grandfather.

33:02.917 --> 33:04.583
Shit.

33:04.585 --> 33:06.385
You left your fingerprints
all over the thing.

33:06.387 --> 33:07.920
Oh, shit!

33:07.922 --> 33:09.788
Yeah.

33:09.790 --> 33:10.989
Find his wallet.

33:10.991 --> 33:13.258
♪♪

33:17.732 --> 33:19.063
[ Grunts ]

33:19.065 --> 33:20.866
♪♪

33:27.608 --> 33:29.073
Got it.

33:29.075 --> 33:31.377
