[ Pounding on door ]

40:59.126 --> 41:00.392
[ Pounding continues ]

41:00.394 --> 41:03.061
Yeah?

41:03.063 --> 41:05.531
Messenger: Mr. Sepp?
Message for you.

41:05.533 --> 41:07.933
♪♪

41:13.273 --> 41:15.407
♪♪

41:20.881 --> 41:22.347
[ Bat thuds ]

41:22.349 --> 41:23.949
♪♪

41:29.423 --> 41:31.724
♪♪

41:43.637 --> 41:47.038
♪♪

41:47.040 --> 41:51.510
♪ Midnight ♪

41:51.512 --> 41:54.245
♪ You've got to get there ♪

41:54.247 --> 41:59.584
♪ At midnight ♪

41:59.586 --> 42:04.189
♪ And you'll be met there
by others ♪

42:04.191 --> 42:06.591
♪ Like you ♪

42:06.593 --> 42:11.062
♪ Brothers, eyes blue ♪

42:11.064 --> 42:15.734
♪ Smiling on the street ♪

42:15.736 --> 42:19.471
♪ I'll dream ♪

42:19.473 --> 42:21.807
[ Indistinct conversations,
dishes clinking ]

42:23.677 --> 42:25.477
Yeah!

42:25.479 --> 42:27.078
Let's hear it for the band!
Come on.

42:27.080 --> 42:28.814
Give a hand for the band!

42:28.816 --> 42:31.082
It feels good to be back
in Los Angeles.

42:31.084 --> 42:33.618
[ Light applause ]

42:33.620 --> 42:34.920
Be right back.

42:36.089 --> 42:38.457
♪♪

42:42.830 --> 42:44.663
♪♪

42:50.371 --> 42:52.504
You sounded real good
up there, Momma.

42:54.508 --> 42:57.308
Like Lena Horne.

42:57.310 --> 43:00.311
Well, you know,
singing's the one thing

43:00.313 --> 43:03.114
that always
came easy for me.

43:03.116 --> 43:05.384
[ Laughs ]

43:05.386 --> 43:06.785
Don't matter
what the song's about,

43:06.787 --> 43:08.587
I can sing it.

43:08.589 --> 43:11.256
You know, Sammy Davis
heard me sing right there?

43:11.258 --> 43:13.592
Right there.
Right here, back in the day.

43:13.594 --> 43:17.462
He came up to me,
gave me his card.

43:17.464 --> 43:20.332
He said he was gonna
take me to Capitol Records.

43:23.003 --> 43:24.703
Sammy Davis.

43:29.543 --> 43:31.343
So, where you been, huh?

43:33.346 --> 43:34.813
Shacked up?

43:34.815 --> 43:40.619
Momma, that man who used to
follow me around in Sparks...

43:40.621 --> 43:45.557
Momma, I need to know
some things about that man

43:45.559 --> 43:47.893
and about George Hodel.

43:50.363 --> 43:52.431
He said your name,
Momma.

43:52.433 --> 43:55.767
I don't know
nothing about it.

43:55.769 --> 43:58.169
-I really need to know --
-You need to know some things?

43:58.171 --> 44:02.774
Yes, I do.
You need to know
how good you got it.

44:02.776 --> 44:04.175
Shoot.

44:04.177 --> 44:06.445
Compared to
Mississippi?

44:06.447 --> 44:08.647
That's not what
I'm talking about, Momma.

44:12.920 --> 44:14.820
Did you know Dr. Hodel?

44:17.658 --> 44:20.259
Did you?

44:20.261 --> 44:22.127
He called you
Mrs. Greenwade.

44:22.129 --> 44:24.129
[ Chuckling ]

44:24.131 --> 44:26.298
♪♪

44:30.804 --> 44:32.671
Come on.

44:32.673 --> 44:33.939
[ Gasps ]

44:38.145 --> 44:41.680
Jimmy Lee: I see you dead
before I let them at you.

44:41.682 --> 44:44.283
I can't protect nothing.
I can't control nothing.

44:44.285 --> 44:47.686
But I<i>can</i>do that.

44:47.688 --> 44:50.555
Violence --

44:50.557 --> 44:53.158
It'll burn your heart,

44:53.160 --> 44:56.662
mark you forever
if you don't let it go.

44:59.366 --> 45:02.567
Now you know something.

45:02.569 --> 45:06.037
